  <article class="container-prose prose-editorial ft-body" set:html={`<h1>Our Commitment to Excellence <br>The B.E.S.T. Oath</h1>				
					<h6>“B.E.S.T.” is the oath every Stairway Mortgage team member signs and carries in their email signature — a daily reminder of who they are and what they stand for. It reflects our culture and our non-negotiable commitment to our clients, our partners, and each other.</h6>				
					<h2>B - Build
</h2>				
									<p>
						We build relationships that honor your vision. Not transactions. Not files. Relationships — the kind where we’re still talking five years after closing because we genuinely care about where you’re going next.					</p>
					<h2>E - Empower
</h2>				
									<p>
						We empower clients with knowledge at every stage of the journey. You will never leave a conversation with us confused about your options. Clear numbers. Honest answers. Full picture — every time.					</p>
					<h2>S - Serve
</h2>				
									<p>
						We serve with compassion, integrity, and care. Serving means showing up before you ask, answering questions you didn’t know to ask, and being there when the process gets hard. That’s the standard.					</p>
					<h2>T - Trust
</h2>				
									<p>
We earn your trust — and we protect it. Trust is not assumed here. It’s built one honest conversation at a time, and we commit to being worthy of it at every step.
					</p>
					<h6>Every employee signs this oath. Every email carries it. Every client interaction is measured against it.</h6>				
					<h3>Meet our Founder
</h3>				
		<p>A Personal Mission. A Clear Philosophy. A Lifelong Partnership in Wealth.</p>Meet Jim Blackburn
					<h3>Founder of Stairway
Mortgage</h3>				
		<p><a href="https://jamesjblackburn.com/jim-blackburn-fort-lauderdale/">Jim Blackburn residing in Fort Lauderdale</a>, is a mortgage strategist, real estate advisor, and financial educator with over two decades of experience helping individuals and families turn everyday real estate decisions into lasting wealth. Jim’s approach isn’t about transactions — it’s about transformation. His mission is to guide people at every stage of their journey, using real estate as a tool to build legacy, purpose, and peace of mind — not just financially, but wholly: with clarity in their finances, confidence in their personal path, and alignment with their spiritual values.</p>		
